        <p class="text-gray-400 leading-loose">My research interests center around autonomous social movements in Mexico City. Through ethnographic research, I aim to understand how these movements construct alternative forms of social organization and power. Specifically, I am interested in the strategies and practices that these movements use to build and sustain autonomy, the relationship between these movements and the state, and the broader implications of these movements for social and political change. By studying autonomous social movements in Mexico City, I hope to contribute to a deeper understanding of how marginalized communities can organize and resist structures of oppression.</p>
